From 71c583074f14a637012b7cd66cc4a8cac2b1220c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sorgelig <pour.garbage@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Jan 2018 11:06:11 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1/1] i2c-designware: quiet the controller-timeout message

Most DE10-Nano boards don't have the optional RTC add-on fitted on
the i2c-gpio bus (see 0004-dts-de10nano-MiSTer.patch's rtc_at_51/68/6F
child nodes), so every boot logs a dev_err "controller timed out" from
the bit-banged i2c-designware-master.c bus scan. Downgrade it to
dev_dbg -- cosmetic, silences boot spam with no add-on board fitted.

Provenance
----------
Origin:       71c583074f14a637012b7cd66cc4a8cac2b1220c
              "Disable RTC error messages." (i2c-designware-master.c half
              only -- the accompanying rtc-m41t80.c hunk is upstream via
              c7622a4e44d9 "rtc: m41t80: reduce verbosity", 2025-05-26,
              and is not carried here.)
              MiSTer-devel/Linux-Kernel_MiSTer, 2018-01-09, against v5.15.
              https://github.com/MiSTer-devel/Linux-Kernel_MiSTer/commit/71c583074f14a637012b7cd66cc4a8cac2b1220c
Author:       Sorgelig <pour.garbage@gmail.com>
Upstream:     No, i2c-designware-master.c half only (verified: the
              "controller timed out" dev_err is still present at its new
              call site, see below). Disposition "carry"
              (docs/patch-provenance.md class F-5).
Forward-port: 5.15 -> 6.18.38, Michael C. Ferguson, 2026-07-12, task P1.9.
              i2c_dw_xfer() was refactored upstream into a small
              i2c_dw_wait_transfer() helper plus a caller that checks its
              return value; the same dev_err -> dev_dbg change is applied
              at the new call site (i2c_dw_xfer(), around the
              i2c_dw_wait_transfer() call), preserving the original's
              intent exactly.

Signed-off-by: Sorgelig <pour.garbage@gmail.com>
[re-anchored for the 7.x beta series: 7.x renamed i2c_dw_init_master() to
 i2c_dw_init(), which appears in both the trailing comment and the call
 immediately after the changed line, so the 6.18 hunk's after-context no
 longer matches at Buildroot's patch -F0. Diff regenerated against
 7.2-rc4; the changed line itself is byte-identical to the 6.18 original
 in ../linux-patches/0030-i2c-designware-quiet-timeout.patch -- keep the
 two in lockstep when editing either. No API divergence beyond context:
 the dev_err -> dev_dbg substitution and its comment are unchanged, and
 the call site is the same i2c_dw_wait_transfer() failure path.]

---
diff --git a/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-designware-master.c b/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-designware-master.c
--- a/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-designware-master.c
+++ b/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-designware-master.c
@@ -771,7 +771,8 @@ i2c_dw_xfer(struct i2c_adapter *adap, struct i2c_msg msgs[], int num)
 	/* Wait for tx to complete */
 	ret = i2c_dw_wait_transfer(dev);
 	if (ret) {
-		dev_err(dev->dev, "controller timed out\n");
+		/* MiSTer: cosmetic -- silence boot spam when no RTC add-on is fitted */
+		dev_dbg(dev->dev, "controller timed out\n");
 		/* i2c_dw_init() implicitly disables the adapter */
 		i2c_recover_bus(&dev->adapter);
 		i2c_dw_init(dev);
